This is one of the two species (along with
P. nigrita
) with a distribution restricted to the highlands and mountains of equatorial East Africa ( Fig. 7B ). Data retrieved from the labels ( N = 20) indicate the vertical range between 1200 and 2300 m a.s.l. The highest precisely recorded collecting site is 2334 m a.s.l. (Aberdare National Park).
